<br>
In this raid we had attendance from people from Finland to Vancouver. Effectively that meant that our top time to do the raid was 7 to 8 hours, as sheer fatigue takes its toll.  Here is an example where without preplanning we could not have all raided together, the GMT side of the pond had to make special arrangements to be with the PST folk. We have great fun together in the Fellowship, but our reality is with the spread in levels and time zones we are not often able to gather, and must preplan.<br>
<br>
But it is encouraging to hear another say we could probably take on larger targets ... personally now that my work schedule has normalized I will be planning a few. Just need to get some clerics some clicky sticks first to make our inevitable rez-learning curve bearable  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
 <p><img border=0 src="http://home.golden.net/~effinger/sig.jpg" /></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jaranna>Jaranna</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/10/03 1:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm59.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=497.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Message to Those Posting Raid Intents</span><hr size=1> This is why I believe all epic mobs should be spawned somehow.  The chances of my getting my epic are very slim, even though it is one of the easiest to get.  I have to kill Venril Sathir and the Broken/Enraged Golem in Fear.<br>
<br>
My guild has a total of 15 members, half of which are alts.  I have to rely on a small network of friends to be able to do anything.<br>
<br>
I have my BCS, and the gnarled staff I could possibly get at some point.  But what are my chances of getting to Fear without a dedicated raiding guild/association?  Very low.<br>
<br>
And even if I could find an open raid, what are the chances the golem's not already taken?  Again, very low.<br>
<br>
I enjoy raiding.  But it's not something I want to do every day.  To me, raiding is the once-every-few-weeks event that I look forward to attending.  It's not my main focus here.  And there are many others like me.<br>
<br>
Without this Battlefield area, those of us in small, family-oriented guilds that do not focus on raiding are pretty much screwed when it comes to doing what we'd like to do.<br>
<br>
It's hard enough trying to get a group of friends and others together to do something as easy as Venril Sathir.  It's very disheartening when you can get them together and the mob with the drop you NEED is gone.<br>
<br>
So, I know how CT feels in that regard.  But I also know that without at least some cooperation from the larger guilds, some of us might as well just reroll as soon as we hit 50.  Because there's really nothing else to do. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://webpages.charter.net/thewok/jarasig.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
